  "text": "Using cross-sectional data covering 147 developed and developing countries, we empirically explore the relationship between government involvement, intelligence and life satisfaction. Investigating the effect of intelligence and government size on life satisfaction contributes greatly to the social sciences; in this vain, the paper explores how the relationship between government and SWB is influenced by a country's average level of intelligence. Our proxy for intelligence is average nation-IQ from [CITATION_1] . To measure government size, we use governments' final consumption expenditures as a percentage of gross domestic product (GDP).",
